codex
I found a stronger oracle-DoS candidate in the math path: the anchor conversion does two unchecked intermediate multiplications before dividing, and the allowed Uniswap V3 tick range is wide enough that a sustained extreme TWAP can overflow those products. I’m quantifying that now because if it holds, it can freeze either one market or the whole reporter set through the shared ETH anchor.
web search: 
web search: calculator: pow(2,128)*1e18*1e18
web search: 
web search: calculator: 2^128 * 10^18 * 10^18
